'''Connor Stuart Roberts''' (born 8 December 1992) is a Welsh professional footballer who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[The New Saints F.C.|The New Saints]].

==Career==

===Youth career===
Roberts began his youth career on the books at his hometown club [[Chirk AAA FC]] before joining [[Tranmere Rovers]] at a relatively early age, then he was signed by [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and would be part of the set up at [[Goodison Park]] for three years. In that time he was part of the development squads and Everton at both Under 18 and Under 21 levels. Roberts also featured in matches for the Everton XI alongside then youth players [[Ross Barkley]] and [[James Wallace (footballer, born 1991)|James Wallace]] but did not break through in similar fashion.

===Burscough & Colwyn Bay loans===
In 2011 Roberts was given the opportunity to gain first team experience at Northern Premier Division side [[Burscough F.C.|Burscough]]. Upon his return to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] he was granted another loan, this time to Conference North side [[Colwyn Bay F.C.|Colwyn Bay]]. He made 4 appearances for the North Wales side in 2011 before returning once more to Merseyside. He was briefly loaned to [[Fulham]] and played for their U18 squad as he featured in the U18 Premier League Final at [[Craven Cottage]] in 2012.

===Cheltenham Town===
Although he signed his first professional contract with Everton in 2011, a season later Roberts joined [[Cheltenham Town F.C.|Cheltenham Town]] in 2012 after being released by the toffees.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cheltenham Town sign ex-Everton goalkeeper Connor Roberts |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19211928 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=10 August 2012 |accessdate=3 May 2014 }}</ref> After a season at the Robins, Roberts failed to make an appearances, however he signed a new one-year contract in July 2013, keeping him at the club until the end of the 2013-14 season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cheltenham Town: Connor Roberts signs new contract |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23160185 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=3 July 2013 |accessdate=3 May 2014 }}</ref> On 3 May 2014, Roberts made his professional debut for Cheltenham in a 3-2 loss against [[Dagenham and Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham and Redbridge]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Cheltenham 2-3 Dag & Red |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27168218 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=3 May 2014 |accessdate=3 May 2014 }}</ref> On 13 May 2014 after two years at [[Whaddon Road]], Roberts was released by Cheltenham.<ref>{{cite news |title=Connor Roberts Released From Cheltenham Town |url=http://www.ctfc.com/news/article/connor-roberts-released-1550275.aspx |work=ctfc.com |publisher=Cheltenham Town |date=13 May 2014 |accessdate=13 May 2014 }}</ref>

In July 2014 he joined [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] on trial and played in a 1-0 win over [[Swansea City F.C.|Swansea City]] under 21s in the Dragons' first pre season friendly. .<ref>{{cite web|title=Wrexham 1 Swansea U21s 0 |url=http://www.wrexhamafc.co.uk/news/article/report-swansea-city-u21s-fr-14.07.12-1751616.aspx |work=Wrexham AFC |accessdate=12 July 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150308233657/http://www.wrexhamafc.co.uk/news/article/report-swansea-city-u21s-fr-14.07.12-1751616.aspx |archivedate=8 March 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> He played in a second game for the Dragons in a 2-0 victory over his former club Colwyn Bay, where he kept a second consecutive clean sheet for [[Kevin Wilkin]]'s side, revealing he wanted to earn a contract at the [[Racecourse Ground]].

===Chester===
On 28 August 2014, Roberts signed for [[Conference Premier]] side [[Chester F.C.|Chester]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Chester: Connor Roberts and Jadan Hall sign |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/28969362 |work=BBC Sport |publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation |date=28 August 2014 |accessdate=28 August 2014 }}</ref>

===Bangor City===
After being released from Chester, Roberts joined [[Bangor City F.C.|Bangor City]] in the Welsh Premier League.

===The New Saints===
In June 2018 he moved to [[The New Saints F.C.|The New Saints]].<ref>http://www.tnsfc.co.uk/2018/06/15/the-new-saints-sign-experienced-keeper/</ref>

===Llandudno===
After making three cup appearances for TNS, Roberts joined [[Llandudno F.C.|Llandudno]] on a short term loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tnsfc.co.uk/2018/11/30/connor-roberts-joins-the-seasiders-on-loan/|title=Connor Roberts Joins The Seasiders On Loan|date=30 November 2018|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut in a 3-0 defeat against [[Connah's Quay Nomads F.C.|Connah's Quay]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.llandudnofc.co.uk/news/llandudno-beaten-by-league-leaders-connahs-quay-2373413.html|title=Llandudno beaten by league leaders Connah's Quay - News - Llandudno Football Club|website=www.llandudnofc.co.uk}}</ref>

==International career==
Roberts qualifies for both Wales and Northern Ireland.<ref>{{cite news |title=Acadrmy Profile Connor Roberts|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/academy/connor-roberts.html |work=evertonfc.com |publisher=Everton FC |date=13 August 2011 |accessdate=3 May 2014 }}</ref> After progressing through the Wales [[Wales national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Wales national under-19 football team|under-19]] teams, Roberts made his debut for [[Wales national under-21 football team|Wales under-21s]] in a 3–0 home friendly victory over [[Iceland national under-21 football team|Iceland]] in February 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title=Wales v Iceland Under 21 Match |url=http://www.faw.org.uk/news/FAW90351.ink |work=faw.org.uk |publisher=Football Association of Wales |date=6 February 2013 |accessdate=3 May 2014 }}</ref>

In May 2014, he received a call up to the [[Wales national football team|Wales]] senior squad for a friendly international against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in early June.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27515345 |title=West Brom goalkeeper Boaz Myhill quits Wales |publisher=BBC Sport |date=22 May 2014 |accessdate=28 May 2014}}</ref>

